{"title": "Unsanitized user input in SQL query", "summary": "  Including unsanitized data, such as user input or request data, in raw SQL queries makes your application vulnerable to SQL injection attacks. ", "description": "\n\nIncluding unsanitized data, such as user input or request data, in raw SQL\nqueries makes your application vulnerable to SQL injection attacks.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid raw queries, especially those that contain unsanitized user input:\n\n```ruby\nUser.where(\"user.email = #{params[:email]}\")\n```\n\n\u2705 Use the ActiveRecord API wherever possible:\n\n```ruby\nUser.where(email: params[:email])\n```\n\n\u2705 Use bind variables:\n\n```ruby\nUser.where(\"user.email = ?\", [params[:email]])\n```\n\n\u2705 Santize the value manually:\n\n```ruby\nUser.where(sanitize_sql([\"user.email = ?\", params[:email]]))\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-89"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_rails_sql_injection", "https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/SQL_Injection", "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/SQL_Injection_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html", "https://guides.rubyonrails.org/security.html#sql-injection"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}